## SSR Hydration: Syncing Browser State

### Pattern: withHooks onInit for Browser-Only APIs

When a signalStore uses browser-only APIs (localStorage, window, document), use `withHooks` to ensure state syncs after SSR hydration:

```typescript
withHooks({
  onInit() {
    // This runs both on server AND client, but browser APIs are
    // unavailable on server, so check environment:
    if (typeof window !== 'undefined') {
      // Client-side only: read from localStorage
      const stored = localStorage.getItem('pus_cookie_consent');
      patchState({
        consentAnswered: stored ? true : false,
        consent: stored as 'all' | 'necessary',
      });
    }
  },
})
```

### Why This Matters
- Server renders with false/default state (no localStorage)
- Client needs to sync actual browser state during hydration
- Without onInit, client never updates, causing ads/features to be invisible
- Place this hook EARLY in the withHooks chain, before other effects

### Symptoms to Watch For
- Feature works on dev (client-only) but not in production (SSR)
- State differs between server render and client inspection
- Silent failures with no console errors

## App Shell Testing: Store Injection Ripple Effect

### Pattern: Mock All Injected Stores

When a store is injected into the root app component (or any shell component), ALL tests that instantiate the app component must provide that store in TestBed:

```typescript
const mockAdsStore = {
  consentAnswered: signal(true),
  targetedAdsConsent: signal(false),
  // ... other signals
};

TestBed.configureTestingModule({
  providers: [
    { provide: AdsStore, useValue: mockAdsStore },
  ],
});
```

### Why This Matters
- Root component injection affects ALL tests that mount that component
- Missing mock → provider not found error → test fails
- This includes indirect tests that render the app (layout tests, routing tests)

### Prevention
- When adding a new store to app root, immediately update app.spec.ts
- Consider: can this store be lazy-loaded instead? (Often yes for non-critical stores)
- If lazy: inject in a feature component, not app root
